Remove GDK_BACKEND workaround for wxGLCanvas

wxgtk3 >= 3.2 no longer need this.

Fix wangqr/Aegisub#155

Fix issues from f8dca9f6386299ec2f90158e2d923a8fb30e3466

Remove deprecated std::iterator
Properly handle Boost::regex_icu
Fix boost/phoenix warnings
Mac: Add CoreAudio player

CMake: Properly build asm file in luajit

The previous trick only works on gcc, as it accepts .s source code

Change default subtitle provider to vsfilter_textsub

We are now directly bundling xy-VSFilter's binary. This is the CSRI name in their dll (and all VSFilter actually)
Change wxmac to wxwidgets for homebrew

Pass storage size to libass to fix rendering

Since ASS rendering depends on the storage size of the video libass
needs to know about it to render the subtitles correctly. If it isn't
told about the storage size libass uses the value from PlayRes{X,Y} as
a guess, but this isn't always correct.
With Aegisub currently always rendering at storage resolution
this ends up the same as the frame size.
